<item>
            <title>[SPARK-2670] FetchFailedException should be thrown when local fetch has failed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2670</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In BasicBlockFetchIterator, when remote fetch has failed, then FetchResult which size is -1 is set to results.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;       &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; None =&amp;gt; {
          logError(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Could not get block(s) from &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + cmId)
          &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; ((blockId, size) &amp;lt;- req.blocks) {
            results.put(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; FetchResult(blockId, -1, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;))
          }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The size -1 means fetch fail and BlockStoreShuffleFetcher#unpackBlock throws FetchFailedException so that we can retry.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But, when local fetch has failed, the failed FetchResult is not set.&lt;br/&gt;
So, we cannot retry for the FetchResult.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
